Press Release




Credit Suisse Trust establishes London Family Office

    Credit Suisse Trust expands its Family Office business by adding a London office. The Family Office of Credit Suisse Trust serves clients with complex family and wealth management issues and assets of more than Euro 50 million. It provides both access to “best in class” professionals as well as the wide range of services and know-how of Credit Suisse Group.








                        Zurich


                        02.11.2001



          Credit Suisse Group, Zurich
          
        T: +41 1 333 8844

Share Buttons



                Close

                Share

            Print




                Send as email



                Share on Facebook



                Tweet this page



                Share on LinnkedIn



                Share on Google+












      On November 6, 2001, Credit Suisse Trust is to officially open its London Family Office located at Five Cabot Square. The London office has been in existence since June 2001 and through this launch adds a new jurisdiction to the Family Office offering. Credit Suisse Trust Family Office is headquartered in Zurich and was founded in 1999. It delivers a wide range of integrated solutions to families or individuals with complex wealth management issues and assets of more than Euro 50 million. The typical client is likely to engage the Family Office during transition periods, e.g. pre-IPO, during sale of corporate assets, acquisition and consolidation, for succession planning or relocation. The clients’ assets are likely to be diverse in nature (corporate, liquid, illiquid, non-financial, intangible etc.) and spread geographically.
      

      The services offered by the Family Office range from strategic wealth planning, comprehensive asset allocation, manager selection and consolidated reporting to optimisation of structures from a legal, tax and family governance perspective. The Family Office of Credit Suisse Trust uses an open architecture approach by offering access to “best in class” professionals in- and outside the Group and is thus solution and not product oriented. At the same time it benefits from the backing and the know-how of one of the largest financial institutions worldwide.
      

      Global Head of the Family Office at Credit Suisse Trust is Babak Dastmaltschi. He joined the company in June from Morgan Stanley. Pierre Gerbier, who also joined Credit Suisse Group in June from Royal Bank of Canada, heads the London Family   Office.
    








        Information about Family Office on Credit Suisse Trust's Website









Credit Suisse Trust
      is a wholly owned subsidiary of the Credit Suisse Group with its headquarter in Zurich, Switzerland, with a history in Switzerland dating back to 1910. One of the leading players in the field, the company offers a comprehensive range of trust and wealth planning services to international clients through its network of branches in Switzerland (Geneva, Lausanne, Lugano) and affiliates abroad (Liechtenstein, Guernsey, Isle of Man, Bahamas, Singapore).
      

Credit Suisse Group
      is a global financial services company domiciled in Switzerland. In the areas of financial services and private banking, it offers investment products and financial advisory services, including insurance and pension solutions, for private and corporate clients. In the area of investment banking, the Group serves global institutional, corporate, government and individual clients in its role as a financial intermediary. It also provides asset management products and services. Credit Suisse Group is headquartered in Zurich and dates back to 1856. Its registered shares (CSGN) are listed on the SWX Swiss Exchange/virt-x, in Frankfurt and Tokyo, and in the form of American Depositary Shares (CSR) in New York. The Group employs around 80,000 staff worldwide and reported assets under management of CHF 1,452.1 billion as of June 30, 2001.
    







